  "text": "Graceful shutdown signal handling across these three Go services demonstrates distinct architectural patterns:\n\n## Kubernetes Graceful Shutdown Architecture\n\n**Signal Registration:** Kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/signal.go implements SetupSignalContext() which uses signal.Notify() to register for SIGTERM and SIGINT (defined in signal_posix.go). The handler creates a buffered channel with capacity 2 to catch both signals - the first triggers graceful shutdown, the second exits immediately.\n\n**Shutdown Orchestration:** The core graceful shutdown logic resides in kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/genericapiserver.go:RunWithContext(). This implements a sophisticated multi-stage shutdown:\n1. ShutdownInitiated signal is fired immediately when signal received\n2. ShutdownDelayDuration (configurable) allows load balancers to detect /readyz failure and drain connections\n3. PreShutdownHooks execute to deregister from service discovery\n4. Connection draining happens in phases:\n   - NonLongRunningRequestWaitGroup waits for regular requests (bounded by RequestTimeout)\n   - WatchRequestWaitGroup drains watch connections with configurable ShutdownWatchTerminationGracePeriod\n5. After draining completes, http.Server.Shutdown() is invoked with ShutdownTimeout (2 seconds when ShutdownSendRetryAfter is enabled)\n6. AuditBackend.Shutdown() is called only after in-flight requests drain\n\nKey shutdown signals: ShutdownInitiated, InFlightRequestsDrained, HTTPServerStoppedListening with timeout coordination to ensure proper ordering.\n\n## Prometheus Graceful Shutdown Pattern\n\n**Signal Registration:** prometheus/cmd/prometheus/main.go (line 1155) uses signal.Notify(term, os.Interrupt, syscall.SIGTERM) with a buffered channel to catch termination signals.\n\n**Shutdown Orchestration:** Uses the 'run.Group' pattern for managing service lifecycle. Key cleanup ordering observed:\n1. Termination handler signals goroutines via context cancellation\n2. Scrape discovery manager stops (cancelScrape())\n3. Notify discovery manager stops (cancelNotify())\n4. Rule manager stops before scrape manager to prevent incomplete rule evaluations\n5. Scrape manager stops (must drain before closing TSDB storage to prevent orphaned writes)\n6. Notifier drains pending notifications on shutdown (DrainOnShutdown configuration at line 582)\n7. Storage backend closes (fanoutStorage.Close())\n\nThe pattern ensures scrape manager stops before storage closes, preventing write errors.\n\n## Grafana Graceful Shutdown Pattern\n\n**Signal Registration:** grafana/pkg/cmd/grafana-server/commands/cli.go:listenToSystemSignals() (line 153) registers separate handlers for SIGHUP and SIGTERM/SIGINT using signal.Notify(). SIGHUP triggers log reloading without shutdown.\n\n**Shutdown Mechanism:** Uses context.WithTimeout(ctx, 30*time.Second) to enforce a 30-second shutdown grace period. The Shutdown method in grafana/pkg/server/server.go coordinates:\n1. BackgroundServices.Shutdown(ctx) is called with the timeout context\n2. Waits for context cancellation or timeout\n3. Logs timeout errors if graceful shutdown exceeds 30 seconds\n4. Uses sync.Once to ensure shutdown runs exactly once\n\nAdditional pattern in grafana/pkg/operators/provisioning/connection_operator.go shows context.WithCancel() for operator shutdown - signal triggers context cancellation which stops all controllers.\n\n## Cross-Service Patterns\n\nAll three services implement:\n- **Double-signal handling:** First signal initiates graceful shutdown, second signal forces immediate exit\n- **Context propagation:** Context cancellation triggers shutdown of dependent components\n- **Timeout enforcement:** Kubernetes uses configurable timeouts per phase, Prometheus uses manager-specific timeouts, Grafana enforces global 30-second timeout\n- **Ordered cleanup:** Drain in-flight requests/connections before stopping background services/storage\n\nKey difference: Kubernetes implements the most sophisticated multi-phase shutdown with explicitly ordered lifecycle signals, while Prometheus and Grafana use simpler context-based cancellation with timeout protection."
